thread.title: Friese sends Hounds to last second victory
thread.title_full: Friese sends Hounds to last second victory

author: CALE AHEARN N-C Correspondent
title: Friese sends Hounds to last second victory
text:
PHOTOS BY BILL SLATTERY Friese 
Cole Friese sent the Homecoming Game crowd home happy with a game-winning 65-yard kickoff return for a touchdown in the final seconds. Tinner 
Linebacker Cameron Tinner hauls down Waynesboro runner Jake Wertz during the Greyhounds’ thrilling 31-27 victory. Gustafson 
Shippensburg wide receiver Cody Gustafson maintains his balance after making one of his game-high 6 catches Friday. Gustafson finished the game with 95 yards and a touchdown. Mills 
Wade Mills (21) and Cole Friese (7) combine to bring down Waynesboro’s Matt Peck Friday. Posted: Tuesday, October 13, 2015 6:00 am Friese sends Hounds to last second victory By CALE AHEARN N-C Correspondent ShipNC.com | 0 comments 
The game looked all but over. Waynesboro, leading 27-24 with less than a minute left, was simply going to squib kick the ball and end the Greyhounds attempt at a comeback victory on Friday.
